The paper presents a new method for reducing the complexity of multi-way fuzzy decision trees in Big Data classification problems. This involves the use of a distributed fuzzy partitioning method and the probability integral transform. The paper is likely to be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) as it deals with classification problems and decision trees. It may also be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves the use of fuzzy sets. Additionally, the paper may be categorized under data mining (cs.DM) as it deals with Big Data classification problems. It may also be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI) as the proposed method can be applied to network data. Finally, it may be categorized under information theory (cs.IT) as the probability integral transform is a concept from information theory.
